Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.48,0:00:06.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.08,0:00:09.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our precious training time...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.45,0:00:13.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We just spent one day in the \NCelestial Spirit World...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.38,0:00:16.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...and three months went by in a flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.75,0:00:18.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.74,0:00:21.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess! I have a proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:25.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Punish me even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.33,0:00:28.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.16,0:02:04.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the wizards' guild \Nknown as Lamia Scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.66,0:02:08.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Grand Magic Games. Every \Nyear we come in second place!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.43,0:02:11.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's shameful and that's no joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.20,0:02:15.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This woman is the master of Lamia Scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.46,0:02:17.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oba Babasama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.81,0:02:21.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until now, I just thought \Nof it as a festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.59,0:02:24.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't afford to \Nthink that way this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.25,0:02:25.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, enough already...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.71,0:02:28.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Obaba's talking to herself again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.29,0:02:32.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lyon! Jura! This time, you're \Ngoing to participate, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:35.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap. I can't refuse Obaba.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.03,0:02:38.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A festival can be nice once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.45,0:02:40.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lyon and Jura-san are \Ngonna be in it this year?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.78,0:02:42.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we'll win it for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.78,0:02:44.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lamia will be Fiore's number one guild!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.75,0:02:47.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you hear?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.02,0:02:51.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that Wizard Saint \NJura-chan from Lamia Scale
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.47,0:02:53.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,is going to be in the Grand Magic Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.17,0:02:59.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This man is Master Bob of the \Nwizards' guild Blue Pegasus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:03.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Men. That is indeed a foul perfume.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.50,0:03:06.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And just when we were aiming \Nfor victory this year...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.20,0:03:10.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll just have to release you-know-who.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.16,0:03:13.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You don't mean...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:18.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Men. A dangerous perfume is raging \Naround the Grand Magic Games this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.19,0:03:24.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And at the wizards' guild called Sabertooth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.72,0:03:26.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sting and Rogue are...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.36,0:03:28.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.62,0:03:31.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu and the others are gonna \Nbe in the Grand Magic Games?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:34.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's the rumor going around Magnolia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:36.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fro heard that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.48,0:03:40.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually lookin' forward \Nto this now, y'know, Rogue?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.82,0:03:42.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.71,0:03:47.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And at yet another wizards' \Nguild, Raven Tail,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.05,0:03:50.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Master Ivan was also making plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:54.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, Makarov. You made \Nme wait seven years...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.43,0:03:56.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the time has finally \Ncome to punish the Fairies,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:59.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,blot them all out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.12,0:04:04.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so looking forward \Nto the Grand Magic Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.08,0:04:09.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just Enough Time to Pass Each Other!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.10,0:04:15.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though there are only five more \Ndays 'til the Grand Magic Games...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:18.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...your magic power hasn't improved at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.19,0:04:23.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like all we can do this \Ntime is rely on the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.45,0:04:28.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The gap between my strength \Nand Lily's has widened again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:31.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You cared about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.05,0:04:36.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, it's not too late! We can \Ntrain like hell these last five days!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.85,0:04:40.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of you steel yourselves! We're \Nnot going to have time to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:43.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza's fighting spirit is on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:47.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good to me! I'm fired \Nup about training like hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:51.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Follow me! We'll start with running!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.22,0:04:57.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A pigeon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.18,0:04:58.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's on its leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:02.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a note! Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.11,0:05:04.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it's a love \Nletter from Gray-sama?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.71,0:05:06.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even close!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.23,0:05:07.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It says here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.70,0:05:12.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Fairy Tail, come to the broken \Nsuspension bridge on the hill."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:13.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do they think they are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.96,0:05:17.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I don't like how \Nthey're givin' us orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.27,0:05:18.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:20.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.41,0:05:21.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, let's check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.90,0:05:23.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it could be a trap...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.77,0:05:26.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I don't think we should go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.49,0:05:27.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll know what it is if we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.85,0:05:30.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! This is gettin' interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.88,0:05:38.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what they meant by \Nthe broken suspension bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.90,0:05:41.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The hell? Nobody's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:43.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so ready for a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.20,0:05:44.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was it, just a prank?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.75,0:05:47.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I said we shouldn't come here, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.86,0:05:49.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:55.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.42,0:05:56.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.44,0:05:57.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It fixed itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.20,0:06:00.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's connected to the other bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.17,0:06:01.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Telling us to cross it then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.23,0:06:04.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This may be a trap after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.54,0:06:06.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.85,0:06:10.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who's behind \Nit, but I say we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.01,0:06:11.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you go first, Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:13.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.05,0:06:20.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't suddenly push me! You \Nscared the crap outta me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.07,0:06:26.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He gets motion sickness \Neven on a hanging bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.98,0:06:31.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, suspension bridge! I'll \Nshow you to underestimate me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:42.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I really thought that anybody who crossed \Nthis bridge would fall down the gorge...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.21,0:06:43.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...but it was okay, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:45.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What am I, a guinea pig?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:47.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Natsu, we know it's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.58,0:06:49.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:53.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, come out, wherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.69,0:06:56.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. And if it's a strong opponent, \Nall the better for our training.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:59.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is training all you think about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.36,0:07:04.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People are over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.29,0:07:05.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:12.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.91,0:07:17.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.29,0:07:20.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...for coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.86,0:07:23.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Fairy Tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:31.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.40,0:07:34.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't changed, Erza.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.30,0:07:38.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you already heard how I escaped?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.68,0:07:39.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:42.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I didn't intend to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.25,0:07:46.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meldy and I broke him out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.57,0:07:48.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.54,0:07:51.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ultear, you did most of it by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.62,0:07:52.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meldy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.54,0:07:56.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Juvia! Long time no see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.80,0:08:03.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She has such a nice smile now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:04.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal escaped from prison?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.74,0:08:06.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're Grimoire...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:09.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, hold on. They're \Nnot our enemies now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.96,0:08:10.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:12.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:16.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've committed a number of sins in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.62,0:08:19.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and I know there's no way I can make \Nup for them with the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:25.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to at least help the \Npeople whose lives I've messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.00,0:08:27.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.28,0:08:30.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People whose lives you've messed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:33.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal, for example...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:37.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't feel guilty. We were both \Npossessed by the dark side.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.90,0:08:39.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.45,0:08:41.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal... Have you regained your memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.29,0:08:43.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It all came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.22,0:08:45.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.91,0:08:51.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My memories returned six years \Nago, while I was in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.77,0:08:56.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza... I really don't know what to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.62,0:09:01.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm responsible for what happened \Nwith the Tower of Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.25,0:09:03.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was manipulating Jellal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.99,0:09:06.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So please don't blame him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.92,0:09:10.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was either going to spend my \Nlife in prison or be executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.19,0:09:13.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I accepted that fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.33,0:09:17.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until Ultear and Meldy \Nbroke me out, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:21.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you've found a purpose to live for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.90,0:09:22.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wendy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.64,0:09:28.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, the Jellal you know \Nseems to be another person entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.21,0:09:31.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I've already solved that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.25,0:09:36.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A purpose to live for... Nothing \Nas noble as that, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.12,0:09:39.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We made a guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.17,0:09:44.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither a proper guild nor a Dark \NGuild... We're an independent guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.03,0:09:48.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A Witch's Crimes... "Crime Sorciere".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:50.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An independent guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.53,0:09:52.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.01,0:09:54.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That you aren't part of an alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.55,0:09:57.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crime Sorciere. I've heard of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.73,0:10:02.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard your guild has destroyed many \Ndark guilds in the last several years!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.96,0:10:05.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have just one purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.70,0:10:06.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Zeref...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.37,0:10:08.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Guilds...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:12.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We formed this guild to drive away \Nall of the darkness from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:17.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So not one more wizard will become \Npossessed by the dark side as we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.18,0:10:21.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.09,0:10:24.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have the Council recognize \Nyou as an official guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.60,0:10:26.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The prison break, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.08,0:10:28.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And we are former members \Nof Grimoire Heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.90,0:10:33.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, official guilds ostensibly have \Nto abide by the Guild Conflict Ban Treaty,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.50,0:10:36.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,even if the other side is a Dark Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.85,0:10:40.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, being independent works for our guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.47,0:10:45.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we didn't call you here \Nto introduce ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:48.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We heard you're going to participate \Nin the Grand Magic Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.54,0:10:50.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.03,0:10:52.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't get near the arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.84,0:10:56.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's one favor we would ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.90,0:10:58.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You want somebody's autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.43,0:11:01.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.76,0:11:05.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, when the Games are held, \Nwe sense a strange magical force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.80,0:11:08.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We want you to get to the bottom of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.04,0:11:17.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.48,0:11:21.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guilds throughout Fiore gather to \Nparticipate in the Grand Magic Games, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:24.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd expect one or two \Nweird kinds of magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.30,0:11:26.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what we thought at first, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.62,0:11:31.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But that magic is evil and \Nsomehow reminds me of Zeref.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:33.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It reminds you of Zeref?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.97,0:11:39.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we're able to sense it because we've \Ngotten too close to Zeref in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.72,0:11:44.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to find out where \Nthat magic is coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:48.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It could give us a clue \Nas to Zeref's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:50.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, this has nothing to \Ndo with the outcome of the Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.51,0:11:55.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be rooting for Fairy \NTail from the sidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.20,0:11:57.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But while you're there, we also want you \Nto search for that mysterious magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.93,0:12:00.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's like grabbing hold of a \Ncloud, but we'll give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.80,0:12:01.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.98,0:12:03.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this, Erza?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.40,0:12:08.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's strange magic present while \Nall the guilds of Fiore are assembled,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.40,0:12:10.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we're at risk, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:12.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll pay your fee in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.62,0:12:13.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Food expenses!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.62,0:12:13.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Rent money!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.89,0:12:15.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't mean money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.56,0:12:21.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My evolved Time Ark will raise \Nthe level of your abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.29,0:12:25.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Power up" has a ring to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:27.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but that's not really what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.11,0:12:33.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wizards have something like a container that \Ndetermines the limit of their magic power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.20,0:12:37.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that container \Nbecomes empty, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.05,0:12:41.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the body will automatically \Nabsorb Eternanos from the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.05,0:12:44.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and after a while, the \Ncontainer will be full again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.53,0:12:49.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But recent research has shown there's \Na part of the container wizards possess
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.36,0:12:52.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that normally doesn't get used.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.80,0:12:58.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something that everyone has. \NLatent ability, Second Origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.25,0:13:00.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Second Origin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.11,0:13:03.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Time Ark will develop that container
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.31,0:13:05.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so you'll be able to use Second Origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:10.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you'll be able \Nto use magic for a longer time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.25,0:13:12.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as employ powerful magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:16.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't get any of that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.02,0:13:20.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you will battle against \Nunimaginably excruciating pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.35,0:13:23.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Her eyes are scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:26.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care! Thank you! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:30.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?! You seem more \Nand more like a real woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.59,0:13:32.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}am{\i0} a woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:34.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still hung up on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.42,0:14:04.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you have to take your clothes off \Nfor the magic characters to be drawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.20,0:14:08.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.79,0:14:13.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there. Bringing out your \Nlatent ability is no simple matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.48,0:14:18.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:20.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How painful is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.65,0:14:22.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to try a Sense Link?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.72,0:14:23.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you out of your mind?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.02,0:14:28.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've also learned how \Nto kid people, huh, Meldy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.95,0:14:31.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to do that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:32.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet I'll cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.47,0:14:34.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're already crying!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.25,0:14:36.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It has nothing to do with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.60,0:14:37.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should just go home...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:42.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.97,0:14:45.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, where's Erza?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.19,0:14:47.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She went somewhere with Jellal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.03,0:14:49.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The two of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.48,0:14:51.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, Juvia and \NGray-sama are going somewhere, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.81,0:14:53.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If what's the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.30,0:14:57.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see she hasn't made any romantic progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.74,0:14:59.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:05.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you got your memories \Nback, right, Jellal?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.51,0:15:07.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.74,0:15:10.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, about Simon, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.80,0:15:14.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.26,0:15:17.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember about Nirvana?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.71,0:15:18.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.50,0:15:22.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember that I had amnesia then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.18,0:15:24.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.03,0:15:28.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I think of you as the "old" \NJellal and treat you that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.31,0:15:33.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That would make me happy... but there's \Nstill what happened with Simon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.09,0:15:36.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't blame you if \Nyou kept your distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:41.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you wish to take \Nrevenge for Simon's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.14,0:15:44.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm prepared to lay down my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.80,0:15:47.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that's what Simon would want?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.27,0:15:52.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You formed a guild in order \Nto destroy Dark Guilds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.46,0:15:56.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how you're atoning for your sins. \N{\i1}That's{\i0} what you're prepared to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.57,0:15:59.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.97,0:16:01.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.82,0:16:06.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, I created Crime Sorciere in \Nthe beginning to make amends for my sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.60,0:16:12.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no way I can make up for \Nwhat I did at the Tower of Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.00,0:16:16.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.29,0:16:19.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get out of this labyrinth of my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.67,0:16:24.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should just die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.65,0:16:36.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you talk so cowardly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.17,0:16:39.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not as strong as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.07,0:16:43.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you can't live if you're \Nnot strong?! Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.98,0:16:45.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Living shows that you're strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:53.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the old Jellal! You're not the \NJellal who struggled desperately to survive!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.70,0:16:56.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be right...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.83,0:16:59.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.16,0:16:59.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.25,0:17:31.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.12,0:17:34.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.64,0:17:38.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In my own clumsy way, I live \Nmy life to the fullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:40.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.23,0:17:43.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.07,0:17:47.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd never see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.56,0:18:02.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.63,0:18:40.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.37,0:18:45.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:52.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no... I, uh, I wasn't thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.24,0:18:55.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's my fault. I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.54,0:18:57.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.90,0:19:02.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?! Congratulations! I didn't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.20,0:19:06.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But of course, yeah. Seven \Nyears have passed, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:16.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she dear to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.90,0:19:19.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:24.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you have to live for her sake, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.39,0:19:29.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.25,0:19:47.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, no one can move.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.81,0:19:50.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why doesn't it affect you like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.38,0:19:53.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the nature of our guild, \Nwe can't stay in one place for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:19:55.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.27,0:19:59.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,About the mysterious magic \Npower at the Grand Magic Games,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.06,0:20:01.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,if you find something out, \Nreport it to us via pigeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.85,0:20:03.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.00,0:20:06.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the competition, we'll be cheering \Nyou on from behind the scenes, so do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.12,0:20:09.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd really like to go see it for myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.54,0:20:10.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go in disguise?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.88,0:20:11.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.95,0:20:15.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll meet again, Erza...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.27,0:20:17.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.20,0:20:19.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Give everyone our regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.39,0:20:22.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And please take care of Gray...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:20:57.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious magic power...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:21:01.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just hope Fairy Tail \Nwon't be put in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.29,0:21:06.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I expect they'll be able to \Nhandle whatever comes their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.30,0:21:09.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! But anyway, Jellal,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.19,0:21:12.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,why did you lie about having a fiancée?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.93,0:21:14.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.60,0:21:17.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you give yourself \Na break once in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.13,0:21:21.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you mean to punish yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.38,0:21:25.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Punishment" is the code of \NCrime Sorciere, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.98,0:21:27.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We decided together, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.22,0:21:31.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't be in love with anyone \Nwho walks in the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.79,0:21:36.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If Erza is happy, that's good enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.75,0:21:40.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, couldn't you have told a better lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.50,0:21:44.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that was low! What, were you \Ntrying to make yourself look cool?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.28,0:21:55.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fiancée, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.70,0:21:59.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You always were lousy at lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.86,0:22:01.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing has changed since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.10,0:22:08.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's better this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.28,0:22:12.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.80,0:22:15.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Erza!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.84,0:23:57.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in Crocus!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.94,0:24:01.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not called the Blooming Capital for \Nnothing! It really is a beautiful city, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.98,0:24:04.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Games are gonna be held here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.38,0:24:07.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm rarin' to go! But who are those guys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.91,0:24:11.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear they're Sabertooth's Dragon Slayers!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.56,0:24:13.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon Slayers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.51,0:24:16.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Crocus, the Blooming Capital!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.85,0:24:19.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, the strange talking cat with them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.64,0:24:22.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,says I look stupid... That I'm an idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.71,0:24:24.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A talking cat... Just like you, Happy.
